Description: Up for auction is my Fender Modern Player Plus Telecaster. My Grandson noted I have three of these in my music room and he asked, "Why?" Well, I love the neck which is Quarter Sawn Maple, the body sculpting, the sound and the Pine body. Don't worry, this is not soft pine, it is Southern Yellow Pine which is called hard pine which is much harder than many hardwoods. It is in player condition with pick marks on the pick guard and minor scuffs in the finish. I could not find any dents but I did not look with a magnifier. Frets are like new. Electronics are original and work as they should. The chrome hardware has some cloudy dull areas that do not rub off. I have no idea what happened but it is there. There are no crack, breaks or repairs. It is all original. This guitar offers a unique mix of Tele and Strat sounds with a little bit of Les Paul with the humbucking bridge pick up. It was made in 2017 according to the serial number. The color is transparent black which is darker than the first stock photo appears on my computer screen. The photos after the first one are the actual guitar. Please excuse the flash artifacts. I had to take the pics indoors. The finish is very high gloss. Shipping is $50.00 to CONUS only. Below is info from Fender. I will not accept returns. Guitar is as described. It plays well. USA ONLY PLEASE. The Fender Modern Player Telecaster Plus HSS offers a rare feature set among Telecaster guitars. This triple-pickup model with a mini-toggle coil-split switch for the Modern Player humbucking bridge pickup. That's a lot of electronics and variety of tone packed into one guitar that's already know for being able to cover a lot of musical ground. This unique model is further distinguished by a pine body whose grain offers a warm look and feel. Other features include C-shaped maple neck, maple fretboard with 9.5" radius and 22 jumbo frets, Modern Player single-coil Telecaster neck pickup and Modern Player Stratocaster middle pickup, five-way pickup switching, three-ply pickguard, knurled "chrome-dome" control knobs, vintage-style Stratocaster string-through-body six-saddle hard-tail bridge, vintage-style tuners and nickel/chrome hardware. Case sold separately.
